reviewText: .Scoring:5 Stars:  Kids - They love Sponge Bob and all his quirky friends!5 Stars  Parents - Shows are good basic fun.4 Stars  Violence - minimal violence, lots of slapstick2 Stars  Educational - Won't get that here!Summary:"Sponge Bob" is a lovable, fun loving sponge who gets into ridiculous situations with his less than dumb best friend "Patrick Star" (starfish) in their hometown of "Bikini Bottom".Other Characters:Adding to the mix are a bunch of real characters like:"Gary", Sponge Bob's pet snail that purrs like a cat;"Sandy Cheeks", a happy and sociable squirrel who lives under water;"Mr. Crabs", the money hungry owner of the Crusty Crab;"Squidward", Sponge Bob's art loving, boring, nasal neighbor who despises Sponge Bob's ridiculous antics;"Plankton", the tiny loud mouthed, one-eyed, single celled, megalomaniac who tries to steal Mr. Crab's crabby patty "secret recipe";Scare Factor:None, except that you and your kids  might become addicted!Violence:Much better than the Bugs Bunny antics we grew up on; the characters show minimal violence towards each other, but enthrall themselves in their hilarious comedic situations.Also see "Nautical Nonesense"

reviewText: Episodes include:Jellyfishing- When Spongebob and Patrick find Squidward is recovering from a bicycling accident, they decide to take him jellyfishing so he can have his best day ever. unfortunately, their good intentions wreak havoc on Squidward's recovery efforts.Dying For Pie- Squidward is guilt ridden when he accidentally lets Spongebob eat an exploding pie. To alleviate his guilt, Squidward resolves to make Spongebob's few remaininghours enjoyable. And boy, does that make Squidward more miserable than ever!Wormy- sandy's taking a trip and puts spongebob and Patrick in charge of her pet caterpillar. When the catterpillar turns into a beautiful butterfly overnight, Spongebob and Patrick are convinced this new creature ate Wormy and is now after them and the rest of Bikini Bottom!F.U.N.- Spongebob is convinced that spongebob's so evil because he's only lonely and needs friends. To prove it, Spongebob befriends Planklton and the two start spending time together. Unfortunately, everyone sees that Plankton is using songebob to get to the secret krabby patty recipe. It's up to Mr. Krabs to reveal Plankton's plot to Spongebob.Club Spongebob- Spongebob and Patrick's clubhouse is atop a really tall tree and there's no room for Squidward. Literally. But Squidward forces his way in, "propelling" the clubhouse into the middle of nowhere. Felling lost, Squidward begins to panic. But Spongebob and Patrick turn their trust in the "magic conch".

reviewText: If you don't think SpongeBob, et al, is funny, you simply don't have a sense of humor. These episodes are cutting edge hilarious and can be enjoyed at every level. The great thing is being able to watch it along with our 3 year old and not being bored senseless as in other shows - the writers have hit the same winning formula as Bugs Bunny - funny to both adults and children but for different reasons. There seems to be something new to catch each time an episode is watched. Two words - buy it!!
